item.description:
@sdouble wrote:

So this kid may not even be yours? And I saw you said you were 19 years old? Honestly, I don’t know whether to believe any of this or not. Most 19 year olds would use some kind of punctuation in their posts. Any at all. The only punctuation I see in yours is “…” which is more like an “uhhhhhhh” than ending a sentence. If this is true, damn. Sorry I doubted you. But since the kid may not even be yours (since she’s already cheated on you in the past), it seems weird she would choose you as the father. You can’t construct a proper sentence, you can barely support yourself, you feel that women should work as well (and judging how this went over with her family, the girl most likely agrees with her mother), and you’re looking for advice on a website that pretty much caters to the needs of people playing a game developed for children ages 14 and under.

This girl is obviously trash, as is her mother and most likely her family. It’s a good idea to move if she’s going to act like that. She’ll be collecting from the government whether you were there or not. That’s just how these people are.
